MODIFICATIONS (Apache-2.0 section 4b): the upstream Plaque Size Tool source in
plaque_size_tool.py has been modified by this project. Changes include:
  - two numerical-precision corrections (un-truncated millimetre values and a
    fixed concentric-duplicate rule) exposed as the "Current" engine; the
    original behaviour is preserved verbatim under the "Published" engine and
    the --published flag;
  - a "Sensitive" engine (lowered size/roundness gates);
  - optional distance-transform watershed splitting of touching plaques;
  - HEIC/HEIF input, millimetre calibration from a user-set dish diameter, and
    within-plate turbidity output.

The optional "Precise" engine (Full build only) additionally incorporates:
  - Ultralytics YOLO (AGPL-3.0) running the PlaqSeg segmentation model;
  - PlaqSeg detector weights and a ResNet-18 classifier trained on the OnePetri
    dataset (Shamash & Maurice 2021; OnePetri code GPL-3.0, dataset
    CC BY-NC-SA 4.0). Weights derived from that data are NonCommercial.

